727602f-a.text: Northern Boulevard, south side, between 77th and 79th Streets, showing in the center of the view the home of F. D. Richardson in 1873. J. Fowler was the owner in 1891. In 1929, it was the Jackson Heights Community Club House. It is not standing in 1938. May 1923. Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

727601f-a.text: Northern Boulevard, north side, east and west of 77th Street (extends northward between the two buildings). In the foreground at the side of J. Pack 's roadhouse of 1891 extended Trains Meadow Road, which was discontinued in 1908 as a street. View 2 looking eastward shows the old Jackson Avenue before it was widened and renamed. Views 1 and 2: March 1924. Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
